### Example of a Function with Control Flow:

def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    priorities = np.zeros_like(bins)
    for i in range(len(bins)):
        if bins[i] + item <= 1:  # Assuming bins are normalized to 0-1
            priorities[i] = 1 - bins[i]  # Prefer less full bins
        else:
            priorities[i] = -1  # Penalize bins that can't fit the item
    return priorities

This function uses a for loop and an if-else condition.

### Another Example:

