So, each function must include at least one control flow statement.

### Another Example:

def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    priorities = np.zeros_like(bins)
    for i in range(len(bins)):
        if bins[i] == 0:
            priorities[i] = 1  # Prefer empty bins
        elif bins[i] + item <= 1:
            priorities[i] = (1 - bins[i]) / (bins[i] + item)
        else:
            priorities[i] = 0
    return priorities

This function uses a for loop and multiple if-else conditions.

