### Approach
The function `priority` takes two arguments: `item` (a single float) and `bins` (a numpy array of floats). The goal is to return a numpy array of the same size as `bins`, where each element represents the priority score of each bin. The priority score is computed using a combination of mathematical operations and numpy functions.

Each implementation must be unique in terms of the combination of operations used. We will use a variety of numpy functions such as `np.exp`, `np.sin`, `np.std`, `np.mean`, `np.max`, `np.min`, `np.abs`, `np.sqrt`, and others to create different priority calculations.

